00:17:38.560 --> 00:17:42.960
If you see a tiger and you start running
in the opposite direction, not a problem.

00:17:42.960 --> 00:17:43.360
Why?

00:17:43.360 --> 00:17:46.960
Because although they both belong
to the cat family,

00:17:46.960 --> 00:17:49.920
those are two
very different situations.

00:17:49.920 --> 00:17:53.600
So that is where this center
comes into play.

00:17:53.600 --> 00:17:59.440
And if there are individuals who react
in a very different way,

00:17:59.440 --> 00:18:02.480
in these kinds of situations,
those are very generic situations,

00:18:02.480 --> 00:18:03.840
very obvious ones.

00:18:03.840 --> 00:18:09.680
But that is what defines a healthy state
of this energy center versus not.

00:18:09.680 --> 00:18:14.000
And therefore, it is very important
to keep this energy center

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:18.400
in a very healthy state
or might say in a balanced state

00:18:18.400 --> 00:18:22.160
by developing through
the Sahaj meditation process,

00:18:22.160 --> 00:18:28.080
what we call a balanced, forgiving
and a charitably disposed personality.

00:18:28.080 --> 00:18:32.240
Because that way, as you can now see
the function of the hypothalamus,

00:18:32.240 --> 00:18:37.680
it does not have to secrete these hormones
that will raise your blood pressure,

00:18:37.680 --> 00:18:42.560
that will raise your heart rate,
that will allow you to react more aggressively

00:18:42.560 --> 00:18:47.120
to an environment which you perceive
to be aggressive,

00:18:47.120 --> 00:18:50.640
which may not be aggressive,
which may not be threatening to you.

00:18:50.640 --> 00:18:56.160
So life then becomes more a matter
of perception rather than reality.

00:18:56.160 --> 00:19:00.560
And the calibration of one's response
to that environment

00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:05.920
is what defines an individual
from being relatively

00:19:05.920 --> 00:19:10.480
what we call in conventional terms
as reactive, immature,

00:19:10.480 --> 00:19:13.600
to somebody who is, we say,
more mature, sagacious.

00:19:13.600 --> 00:19:17.280
So think of a Lincoln
or a Gandhi like personality

00:19:17.280 --> 00:19:23.440
relative to somebody who is
much more reactive or gets easily ruffled,

00:19:23.440 --> 00:19:27.680
we say, we just know some people
who are just calm, more composed,

00:19:27.680 --> 00:19:32.160
they don't react that negatively
or excessively.

00:19:32.160 --> 00:19:37.600
And that is where it kind of comes in,
the importance of this center

00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:44.160
to maintain that balance within us,
right action and right behavior.

00:19:44.160 --> 00:19:47.120
It does not mean
we remain constantly passive.

00:19:47.120 --> 00:19:50.223
It does not mean
we remain constantly active.

00:19:50.223 --> 00:19:52.000
Where is that fine balance?

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:54.640
How do you calibrate
back to that aircraft?

00:19:54.640 --> 00:19:59.280
How do you maintain your speed,
your altitude and your course

00:19:59.280 --> 00:20:02.480
from a, shall we say,
an emotional perspective

00:20:02.480 --> 00:20:08.080
or from a spiritual perspective
is what this center is really about.

00:20:08.080 --> 00:20:14.720
And that's why it plays such a vital role
in human spirituality.

