00:21:15.760 --> 00:21:18.720
People had a much more
quote-unquote pastoral lifestyle,

00:21:18.720 --> 00:21:20.640
certainly pre-industrial societies.

00:21:20.640 --> 00:21:27.120
But even in post-industrial societies,
it was not that much of a deal.

00:21:28.000 --> 00:21:32.560
This influence of media
and the environment around us,

00:21:32.560 --> 00:21:34.800
there were communities,
there were neighbors,

00:21:34.800 --> 00:21:41.360
but with the advent of social media,
particularly, life has become very reactive.

00:21:41.360 --> 00:21:45.600
You are part of some kind of
a social media platform,

00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:50.080
whichever it is, with your friends,
with your office colleagues or neighbours,

00:21:50.080 --> 00:21:54.880
as the case may be,
you read a post about a topic,

00:21:54.880 --> 00:21:58.960
whether it is political, whether it is social,
whether it is cultural,

00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:02.240
and the brain processes it.

00:22:02.240 --> 00:22:05.600
Within our brain is a very
important group

00:22:05.600 --> 00:22:08.480
of neurotransmitters -
one of them is dopamine.

00:22:08.480 --> 00:22:13.200
Dopamine is a pleasure giving molecule.

00:22:13.200 --> 00:22:16.880
Whenever we do or feel
something pleasurable,

00:22:16.880 --> 00:22:21.280
there is a part of the brain called
a substantia nigra that secretes dopamine.

00:22:21.280 --> 00:22:24.320
Dopamine gives us that high, that rush.

00:22:24.320 --> 00:22:30.000
And where social media comes in,
social media algorithms.

00:22:30.000 --> 00:22:33.680
I'm not a tech expert,
but I saw a couple of documentaries,

00:22:33.680 --> 00:22:40.960
and they explained beautifully
that there is a full blown understanding

00:22:40.960 --> 00:22:47.600
of the human nervous system,
and particularly of how the dopamine

00:22:47.600 --> 00:22:50.800
system works to produce that rush.

00:22:50.800 --> 00:23:00.400
So we are constantly through algorithms
that are designed to generate that rush within us.

00:23:00.400 --> 00:23:03.520
So we are constantly hooked onto it.

00:23:03.520 --> 00:23:08.480
We are given content or fed content
that is based on these algorithms

00:23:08.480 --> 00:23:12.000
that grab our attention and hold it.

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:17.440
And that is where this center is also
where it's damaged the most,

00:23:17.440 --> 00:23:20.320
because it keeps us on this endless loop.

00:23:20.320 --> 00:23:26.560
We are essentially like animals
that are on treadmills,

00:23:26.560 --> 00:23:33.680
that you're constantly fed
that morphine of information, if you will,

00:23:33.680 --> 00:23:36.880
and that triggers dopamine within us.

00:23:36.880 --> 00:23:42.560
And that gives us that sense of high
and that high keeps us hooked onto social media.

00:23:42.560 --> 00:23:50.160
So the Agnya Chakra or the sixth energy center
probably in the entirety of human civilization,

00:23:50.720 --> 00:23:54.320
recorded and unrecorded history,
and this is not a hyperbole,

00:23:54.320 --> 00:23:59.200
I genuinely feel it has never probably
been more stressed due to social media.

00:23:59.200 --> 00:24:00.480
But what is the solution?

00:24:00.720 --> 00:24:04.000
It's easy to identify a problem,
but then what is the solution?

00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:07.120
The solution is that through meditation,

00:24:07.120 --> 00:24:12.160
we can begin to stay away from that rush.

00:24:12.160 --> 00:24:14.080
We don't need that rush.

00:24:14.080 --> 00:24:18.320
You don't need to constantly feel
your presence on social media

00:24:18.320 --> 00:24:23.280
or see what is the
latest post out there?

00:24:23.280 --> 00:24:26.320
Or if you posted something,
has somebody read it or not?

00:24:26.320 --> 00:24:28.080
How many likes have you received?

00:24:28.080 --> 00:24:29.680
Or have you not received it?

00:24:29.680 --> 00:24:32.560
So if you have not received anything,
no responses,

00:24:32.560 --> 00:24:35.360
you kind of go down and then
that dopamine rush goes down,

00:24:35.360 --> 00:24:36.720
you'll start feeling depressed.

00:24:36.720 --> 00:24:39.120
And we see this particularly in teenagers,

00:24:39.120 --> 00:24:42.240
which is why the US Congress
is acting very wisely.

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:47.680
So to try to see if these
social media platforms

00:24:47.680 --> 00:24:50.878
can actually be modulated

00:24:50.878 --> 00:24:55.489
to avoid creating mental health issues

00:24:55.489 --> 00:24:59.920
for susceptible age groups
such as teenagers,

00:24:59.920 --> 00:25:05.120
whose use can lead to extreme outcomes.

00:25:05.120 --> 00:25:08.240
So yes, that's a phenomenal point
that you raised.

00:25:08.240 --> 00:25:13.360
And this energy center in particular
plays a very critical role

00:25:13.360 --> 00:25:18.480
in either being susceptible
and being influenced by social media.

00:25:18.480 --> 00:25:22.240
But then through meditative practice,
such as the Sahaj meditation,

00:25:22.240 --> 00:25:26.240
you can actually maintain
a healthy boundary.

00:25:26.240 --> 00:25:29.600
So nobody's saying here,
you should not interact with social media,

00:25:29.600 --> 00:25:32.640
not use social media,
social media is a way of life now.

00:25:32.640 --> 00:25:34.160
We all have to live with it.

